			<div id = "comment-22881" class = "comment">
				<p>I guess that depends on the robot you use and its usage scenario - if you need pinpoint precision in order for the robot to complete its assignment according to specifications, then a real-time system is probably the way to go. If on the other hand you can live with some data points not arriving, e.g. because you use time-tracking and may interpolate accurately enough, then you don't require a (hard) real-time system</p>
